OL,3,CChurch of England apologises for
OL,4,C'shameful' role in forced adoption
OL,6,FITV News has heard heartbreaking
OL,7,Ftestimony from survivors of historical
OL,8,Fforced adoption, Social Affairs
OL,9,FCorrespondent Sarah Corker and Senior
OL,10,FProducer Lottie Kilraine report
OL,12,FThe Church of England has "profoundly"
OL,13,Fapologised for the first time for "the
OL,14,Fpain, the trauma and the stigma"
OL,15,Fsuffered by tens of thousands of women
OL,16,Fand their children, now adults, by
OL,17,Fhistorical forced adoption.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1781866972
OL,3,CChurch of England apologises for
OL,4,C'shameful' role in forced adoption
OL,6,FIn an interview with ITV News, the
OL,7,FArchbishop of Canterbury Sarah
OL,8,FMullally acknowledged the Church's
OL,9,Fcentral role in the scandal and said
OL,10,Fsurvivors "have nothing to be ashamed
OL,11,Fof", adding: "the shame is ours".
OL,13,FThursday's announcement comes after a
OL,14,Flong-running ITV News investigation
OL,15,Fhas laid bare the trauma and neglect
OL,16,Ffaced by both mothers and their
OL,17,Fchildren, now adults, many of whom are
OL,18,Fstill searching for answers or have
OL,19,Fsince died.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1781866972
OL,3,CChurch of England apologises for
OL,4,C'shameful' role in forced adoption
OL,6,FWhen pressed on why it has taken so
OL,7,Flong for survivors who have been
OL,8,Fcampaigning to receive an apology for
OL,9,Fdecades, Archbishop Mullally said that
OL,10,Fit was a "deep regret that this comes
OL,11,Ftoo late for some people".
OL,13,FBetween 1949 and 1976, an estimated
OL,14,F250,000 pregnant women and girls were
OL,15,Fsent away to "prison-like" homes run
OL,16,Fby the church and state and had their
OL,17,Fbabies put up for adoption. Other
OL,18,Finfants died due to mistreatment or
OL,19,Fpoor care.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1781866972
OL,3,CChurch of England apologises for
OL,4,C'shameful' role in forced adoption
OL,6,FThe Church of England ran more than
OL,7,F200 mother and baby institutions for
OL,8,Ffour decades and 30 adoption agencies
OL,9,Fover nearly five decades, of which
OL,10,Ftheir own research shows affected
OL,11,F"tens of thousands of people".
OL,13,FIn 2024, ITV News uncovered mass
OL,14,Funmarked graves of babies who died in
OL,15,Ffive of their homes amid allegations
OL,16,Fof poor treatment and abuse in
OL,17,FCumbria, Winchester, Northampton and
OL,18,FNorthamptonshire and Essex.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1781866972
OL,3,CChurch of England apologises for
OL,4,C'shameful' role in forced adoption
OL,6,FThursday's announcement is the first
OL,7,Ftime the church has directly admitted
OL,8,Fit "does bear responsibility for the
OL,9,Fway in which women and children did
OL,10,Fnot receive the care and support that
OL,11,Fthey should have done".
OL,13,F"We are, we take our responsibility
OL,14,Fand would play any part that we would
OL,15,Fneed to play in any further
OL,16,Finvestigation," Archbishop Mullally
OL,17,Fsaid.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1781866972
OL,3,CChurch of England apologises for
OL,4,C'shameful' role in forced adoption
OL,6,FWhile some campaigners have welcomed
OL,7,Fthe apology, others have said
OL,8,Fcriticised the announcement and
OL,9,Fdisputed that the process has been
OL,10,Fsurvivor-informed.
OL,12,F"An apology about us, without us, is
OL,13,Fnot accountability," a spokesperson
OL,14,Ffor the Adult Adoptee Movement (AAM)
OL,15,Fsaid.
OL,17,F"The Church has demonstrated that they
OL,18,Fare not yet ready to listen, reflect
OL,19,For change. We are sad to say, this
OL,20,Fstatement is an insult to survivors."
OL,26,@tD@AOUuD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/22
