OL,3,CChurch of England apologises for
OL,4,C'shameful' role in forced adoption
OL,6,F'I never even had the chance to see my
OL,7,Fdaughter'
OL,9,FIn the late 1960s Felicity Davies from
OL,10,Fthe Wirral was aged 15 when her baby
OL,11,Fwas taken for adoption. The trauma of
OL,12,Fthat day has never left her.
OL,14,FShe was sent to Chaddeslode House in
OL,15,FShrewsbury, an institution for
OL,16,Funmarried mothers run by the Church of
OL,17,FEngland.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1781866972
OL,3,CChurch of England apologises for
OL,4,C'shameful' role in forced adoption
OL,6,FForced to scrub floors, carry out
OL,7,Fmenial tasks and go to the chapel to
OL,8,Fpray for forgiveness, the women there
OL,9,Fwere given no choice - adoption was
OL,10,Fthe only option.
OL,12,F"The moment of goodbye was awful," Mrs
OL,13,FDavies told ITV News. "I remember
OL,14,Fstanding outside the hospital waiting
OL,15,Ffor a bus and feeling a part of me was
OL,16,Fmissing.
OL,18,F"I howled. Baby Mary was five weeks
OL,19,Fold. The social worker told me I have
OL,20,Fto never see her again, it was like
OL,21,Fbeing punched in the stomach."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
