OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1781866972
OL,3,CChurch of England apologises for
OL,4,C'shameful' role in forced adoption
OL,6,F"I would like to say that we are
OL,7,Fprofoundly sorry," she said. "That
OL,8,Fdiscrimination then and today is
OL,9,Fcompletely unacceptable and
OL,10,F(survivors) have nothing to be ashamed
OL,11,Fof. The shame is ours."
OL,13,F'Dehumanising and dismissive attitudes'
OL,15,FThe Church has spent six months going
OL,16,Fthrough its extensive archives, which
OL,17,Finclude thousands of pages of
OL,18,Fdocuments relating to it's mother and
OL,19,Fbaby homes and the adoption agencies,
OL,20,Fto better understand the scale of it's
OL,21,Finvolvement.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
